feed.title: Xanadu Expands Partnership with A*STAR to Advance Photonic Quantum Computing
feed.summary: Xanadu Quantum Technologies Inc. has expanded its partnership with Singapore's Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR) through a new Memorandum of Understanding. This collaboration aims to advance research and development in quantum technologies, building on previous work with A*STAR's Institute of Microelectronics and now including the Institute of High Performance Computing and Quantum Innovation Centre. The partnership seeks to accelerate the development of fault-tolerant photonic quantum computers and explore potential joint quantum laboratories in Singapore.

feed.title: Crane Harbor and Xanadu Submit Draft to SEC
feed.summary: Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. Class A (CHAC) and Xanadu Quantum Technologies Inc. have confidentially submitted a draft registration statement to the SEC for their proposed business combination. The deal, expected to close by Q1 2026, aims to make Xanadu the first publicly traded photonic quantum computing company with an anticipated market capitalization of $3.6 billion and $500 million in capitalization for the combined entity. Xanadu, founded in 2016, specializes in room-temperature photonic quantum computing and quantum software development.

feed.title: Crane Harbor and Xanadu Submit Draft to SEC
feed.summary: Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. (CHAC) and Xanadu Quantum Technologies Inc. have confidentially submitted a draft registration statement to the SEC for their proposed business combination. This transaction aims to make Xanadu the first publicly traded pure-play photonic quantum computing company, with an anticipated pro forma market capitalization of $3.6 billion and approximately $500 million in capitalization for the combined entity. The deal is expected to close by the end of Q1 2026.

feed.title: Crane Harbor and Xanadu Announce Business Combination
feed.summary: Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. (CHAC) and Xanadu Quantum Technologies have announced a business combination, making Xanadu the first publicly traded pure-play photonic quantum computing company. The deal, valued at approximately $3.1 billion, is expected to provide Xanadu with $500 million in gross proceeds to develop fault-tolerant quantum computers. This move positions Xanadu at the forefront of the quantum computing industry, leveraging its innovative photonic technology and widely used PennyLane software.

feed.title: Xanadu to go public on Nasdaq and TSX in $3.6-billion USD SPAC deal
feed.summary: Toronto-based quantum computing firm Xanadu plans to go public on the Nasdaq and Toronto Stock Exchange through a merger with special purpose acquisition company (SPAC) Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. This $3.6-billion USD deal aims to raise $500 million USD, accelerating Xanadu's development of fault-tolerant photonic quantum computers and making it the first Canadian tech company to debut on the TSX in over four years. The company will use the proceeds to expand its hardware development, facilities, and software offerings, with significant investment from both new and existing investors.

feed.title: Xanadu Quantum Technologies Inc entered into a definitive business combination agreement to acquire Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. from Xanadu Quantum Technologies Inc. for $3 billion in a reverse merger transaction.
feed.summary: Xanadu Quantum Technologies Inc. has announced a definitive business combination agreement to acquire Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. in a $3 billion reverse merger. The transaction, expected to close in Q1 2026, aims to accelerate the development and deployment of Xanadu's photonic quantum computer systems. Upon closing, the combined company's shares are anticipated to trade on both the Nasdaq Stock Market and the Toronto Stock Exchange.

feed.title: Certain Class B Ordinary Shares of Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. are subject to a Lock-Up Agreement Ending on 22-OCT-2025.
feed.summary: Certain Class B Ordinary Shares of Crane Harbor Acquisition Corp. are subject to a lock-up agreement ending on October 22, 2025. These shares will be under lockup for 181 days from April 24, 2025, to October 22, 2025. The agreement restricts the sponsor, directors, and officers from selling, pledging, or disposing of these shares without prior written consent.
